      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD ODDS ROCKY (3) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at Wentworth Park in a handy 29.72 beating Zipping Violet. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Sure to prove hard to beat. PARTY STARTED (6) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Paw Estrella (24.69) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Solid formlines coming through her last run. Expected to feature again. GALLOPING JESSIE (1) stalked the lead from the inside draw then took over turning and burst clear to score (24.20) at Traralgon in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 over 425m. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Leading chance again. DR. WARREN (7) is another with top-three prospects.",
